results.name: Number of triples {x, y, x mod y} of three distinct divisors of n.
comment: a(n) = 0 if n is a prime power. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Aug 20 2015
link: Charles R Greathouse IV, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: a(6) = 1 because x = 3, y = 2, x mod y = 1 and 3, 2, 1 are distinct divisors of 6.
program: (PARI) a(n)=my(d=divisors(n),x,y,z); sum(i=2,#d-2, y=d[i]; sum(j=i+1,#d-1, x=d[j]; z=x%y; z && n%z==0)) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Aug 20 2015
